{"ts":"2026-07-11T18:01:34.472Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-hous"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"GH-514: pm init writes no .gitignore rules — runtime/search caches churn as tracked files in downstream repos"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"GH-514 reports pm init writing a malformed .gitignore line concatenating .agents/pm/search/ + .agents/pm/runtime/metadata-cache-bodies.json. Source evidence: the block header string ('PM CLI runtime and cache files') has NEVER existed in this repo history (git log -S empty; zero hits in src/dist/packages/plugins) — pm init currently writes NO .gitignore entries at all. The malformed block in the reporting repo (simworld) was authored by external tooling. The real defect this issue surfaces: because pm init owns no ignore rules, repos that version .agents/pm get spurious churn on runtime/metadata-cache*.json and search/ caches with every command, and users/agents hand-write (and garble) ignore blocks. Fix = pm init owns a canonical idempotent fenced block + a health/validate check for already-tracked cache files. Related: pm-4det (this repo untracked its own caches), GH-501/pm-69nl (init discovery)."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["dx","gh-issue","init","onboarding"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-11T18:01:34.472Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-11T18:01:34.472Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":90},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"pm init (workspace and path-target modes) idempotently writes a canonical fenced ignore block covering .agents/pm/runtime/ and .agents/pm/search/ into the repo .gitignore (creating it if absent), one path per line; Re-running pm init never duplicates or garbles the block (fence markers; existing malformed concatenated lines inside the fence are replaced); pm validate or pm health warns when tracked .agents/pm runtime/search cache files exist in git (the already-tracked case a blanket ignore cannot fix), with a remediation hint (git rm --cached); Docs (init + getting-started) document the ignore block and the tracked-cache remediation"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"low"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"medium"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"4caef3b2c5b40a66e1dffc53b09d030d483208231848b95b8791fe823810173c","message":""}
